curam.util.common.domain

Interface DomainNames


  • public interface DomainNames
    An interface defining constants for the names of the infrastructure domains. Sub-interfaces are used for the "core" domains and their subset, the "root" domains. Unless specifically interested in the root domains because they are root domains, it is preferable to use DomainNames.Core to access the domain names.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  DomainNames.Core
      Core domain names are supported by the infrastructure, but they are not necessarily root domains.
      static interface  DomainNames.Root
      Root domains do not share a common ancestor domain and provide the base from which all other domains are derived directly or indirectly.
